        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Collier refers to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> and to <hi rend="italic">Punishments in education</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1508.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Collier 1872</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 310–11, CD had argued that not only was blushing involuntary, but attempts to restrain it would actually increase the tendency.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, p. 86, CD had written that barking was not natural to any species of <hi rend="italic">Canis</hi> except for <hi rend="italic">C. latrans</hi> (the coyote). Red foxes belong to the genus <hi rend="italic">Vulpes</hi>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 2: 242.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">Blink Bonny won the Derby in 1857, Blair Athol (her son) in 1864, and Gladiateur in 1865 (Horseracing history online (The National Horseracing Museum, Newmarket, www.horseracinghistory.co.uk; Thoroughbred heritage, www.tbheritage.com (accessed 14 November 2011)). Eclipse (born 1764) won at Epsom Downs at the age of 5 years and won seventeen later races, retiring to stud at the age of 6 (Vamplew and Kay 2005).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">In horse-racing, a plater is a horse that competes in plate (i.e., minor) races, but can also refer more generally to an inferior racehorse (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5936.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">OED</hi></ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
